# fVDB build patches — machine-specific, version-pinned reference

These 4 patches were needed to build the real fVDB library (`xcube/`'s
dependency: `fvdb.nn.VDBTensor`, missing from the publicly installable
`fvdb_core` package) from source, from a specific historical PR of
AcademySoftwareFoundation/openvdb (`pull/1808/head`, branch `feature/fvdb`),
cloned into `openvdb/` (gitignored — a separate third-party library, not
part of this repo). See PROGRESS.md's "Environment setup" section for the
full narrative context.

**This patch is captured against one specific toolchain and is NOT
guaranteed to apply cleanly, or even be the right fix, on a different
combination of versions.** These are version-drift fixes (a removed torch
API, a changed CUDA/cuBLAS enum, a duplicate pybind11 type caster) — if any
of the versions below differ on the machine you're reading this on, treat
this file as a *reference for the kind of fix needed*, not a blind
copy-paste. Re-derive from the actual build error first; only reach for
this diff if your versions match exactly.

Captured 2026-07-24 on this machine, against:
  - PyTorch:  2.10.0 (built against CUDA 12.9)
  - CUDA toolkit used for the JIT/build (NOT the default `nvcc`):
              /usr/local/cuda-12.4, release 12.4.131 — this project pins
              PATH=/usr/local/cuda-12.4/bin explicitly (see PROGRESS.md);
              the machine also has a separate default CUDA 12.9 install
              that is NOT what fVDB was built against.
  - Host compiler: gcc-12 / g++-12 (Ubuntu 12.3.0-1ubuntu1~22.04.3) — the
              conda env's own bundled gcc (14.3.0) is too new for CUDA 12.4
              and was rejected by nvcc; forcing CC/CXX=gcc-12/g++-12 fixed it.
  - pybind11: 3.0.1
  - openvdb/fvdb commit: 7c04e6d ("Update setup.py"), branch feature/fvdb

To apply on a matching machine (from inside the openvdb/ clone), strip this
header first, then apply the remaining diff hunks:
  sed -n '/^--- PATCH BODY BELOW ---$/,$p' fvdb_build_patches.diff | tail -n +3 | git apply -
(or just read the 4 hunks below and make the equivalent edits by hand —
it's only ~80 lines total across 4 files.)

--- PATCH BODY BELOW ---

diff --git a/fvdb/setup.py b/fvdb/setup.py
index f2b7f9a..85325ea 100644
--- a/fvdb/setup.py
+++ b/fvdb/setup.py
@@ -138,7 +138,7 @@ class FVDBBuildCommand(cpp_extension.BuildExtension):
 
         # Find all the headers and copy them into the build directory.
         # This way extension modules of FVDB can include them.
-        nanopath = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)), '..', 'nanovdb')
+        nanopath = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)), '..', 'nanovdb', 'nanovdb')
         fvdb_headers = get_header_files_recursive('src', 'fvdb')
         nanovdb_headers = get_header_files_recursive(nanopath, 'nanovdb')
 
diff --git a/fvdb/src/detail/GridBatchImpl.cu b/fvdb/src/detail/GridBatchImpl.cu
index b78ac61..81d9093 100644
--- a/fvdb/src/detail/GridBatchImpl.cu
+++ b/fvdb/src/detail/GridBatchImpl.cu
@@ -114,7 +114,11 @@ void GridBatchImpl::recomputeBatchOffsets() {
 
 
 torch::Tensor GridBatchImpl::gridToWorldMatrix(int bid) const {
-    return torch::linalg::inv(worldToGridMatrix(bid));
+    // Original: return torch::linalg::inv(worldToGridMatrix(bid));
+    // torch::linalg::inv (a convenience C++ wrapper) was removed from libtorch's headers
+    // in newer PyTorch versions. The underlying matrix-inverse operation itself still
+    // exists, just under a different name: at::linalg_inv.
+    return at::linalg_inv(worldToGridMatrix(bid));
 }
 
 c10::intrusive_ptr<GridBatchImpl> GridBatchImpl::clone(torch::Device device, bool blocking) const {
diff --git a/fvdb/src/detail/ops/convolution/backend/MESparseConvolution.cu b/fvdb/src/detail/ops/convolution/backend/MESparseConvolution.cu
index 55f61f1..a5cde20 100644
--- a/fvdb/src/detail/ops/convolution/backend/MESparseConvolution.cu
+++ b/fvdb/src/detail/ops/convolution/backend/MESparseConvolution.cu
@@ -85,7 +85,11 @@ void gpu_gemm<at::Half>(const cublasOperation_t transA, const cublasOperation_t
   int lda = (transA == CUBLAS_OP_N) ? K : M;
   int ldb = (transB == CUBLAS_OP_N) ? N : K;
   cublasMath_t cublas_flags = CUBLAS_DEFAULT_MATH;
-  if (!at::globalContext().allowFP16ReductionCuBLAS()) {
+  // Original: if (!at::globalContext().allowFP16ReductionCuBLAS()) {
+  // allowFP16ReductionCuBLAS() used to return bool (true = reduced-precision allowed);
+  // newer libtorch returns a 3-way enum instead. AllowReducedPrecisionWithSplitK is the
+  // enum value matching the old "true", so "not equal to that" matches the old "!...".
+  if (at::globalContext().allowFP16ReductionCuBLAS() != at::CuBLASReductionOption::AllowReducedPrecisionWithSplitK) {
     cublas_flags = static_cast<cublasMath_t>(cublas_flags | CUBLAS_MATH_DISALLOW_REDUCED_PRECISION_REDUCTION);
   }
 
diff --git a/fvdb/src/python/TypeCasters.h b/fvdb/src/python/TypeCasters.h
index a8d37bb..2e8da5f 100644
--- a/fvdb/src/python/TypeCasters.h
+++ b/fvdb/src/python/TypeCasters.h
@@ -35,27 +35,10 @@ public:
 };
 
 
